<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-07T11:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-07T11:30:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1042: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-07T12:00:00-04:30">February 7,
                                1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3. Department’s telegram 1, February 6, 6 p.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d472fn3">It read “Your No. 2, February 3, 5 p.m. Was
                                Venezuelan telegram to Peru based on Kellogg Pact? This is
                                important.” (721.23/994)</note> Message to Peruvian Government
                            delivered through Venezuelan Legation in Lima supported Brazilian
                            proposal and American note. No instructions were given to mention
                            Kellogg Pact.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>